  <title>What is GêBR?</title>
  <para>GêBR is a simple graphical interface which 
    <emphasis role="bold">facilitates geophysical data processing</emphasis>. GêBR is 
    <emphasis role="bold">not a package for processing</emphasis>, it is designed to 
    <emphasis role="bold">integrate</emphasis> a large variety of free processing packages, such as 
    <emphasis>Seismic Un*x</emphasis> and 
    <emphasis>Madagascar</emphasis>.</para>
  <para>GêBR can manage Projects and Lines, assemble and execute Flows and follow the results of
    your data processing. Everything in a simple and friendly way.</para>
  <para>Being a 
    <emphasis role="bold">free software</emphasis>, anyone can use and customize GêBR for free,
    according to the terms of the 
    <emphasis>GNU Public License</emphasis>. That makes this software very attractive for academic
    research and for use in courses.</para>
  <section>
    <title>GêBR Project</title>
    <para>Our main objective is to help bring together the Brazilian
      geophysics community, by developing tools to aid in the dissemination of research in the
      area.</para>
    <para>For more information, visit the project's official site:
      <emphasis>
        <link xlink:href="http://www.gebrproject.com">www.gebrproject.com</link>
    </emphasis>.</para>
  </section>
  <section>
    <title>What's new in version 0.16.0</title>
    <para>The release of GêBR (0.16.0) suffered some changes. GêBR is more stable and present
      some new functionalities:</para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>The maestro concept is born allowing to execute GêBR jobs in multiples machines.
        (see 
        <xref linkend="servers_configuration" />and 
        <xref linkend="multiple_machines" />).</listitem>
      <listitem>Now it is possible to control the number of cores used by the jobs of GêBR and
        change the priority of execution of a job (see 
        <xref linkend="multi_cores" />and 
        <xref linkend="priority_execution" />).</listitem>
      <listitem>Renewed interface adds new functionalities and improve usability in
        GêBR.</listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>
